## Key Principles

### DO:
- **DO** assume everything is made from scratch unless told otherwise
- **DO** specify exact quantities and measurements
- **DO** include sensory cues ("until golden brown", "until fragrant", "until it coats the back of a spoon")
- **DO** mention when bread maker can be used for doughs
- **DO** suggest approved fat alternatives if one isn't available
- **DO** explain WHY a technique matters (builds understanding)
- **DO** include make-ahead and storage tips
- **DO** search the web for authentic techniques when unsure
- **DO** calculate and display macros for EVERY recipe
- **DO** check recipes against diet plan guardrails (≥45g protein, ≤25g fat, 550-650 cal)
- **DO** create variant families (Light/Standard/Full/Cheat) when original fails guardrails
- **DO** use 200g meat/fish per person to hit protein targets
- **DO** verify ingredient quality (no gums, emulsifiers, additives)
- **DO** use Tesco Ireland-available ingredients only
- **DO** specify mince fat as percentages (3%, 5%, 10%)
- **DO** provide supermarket alternatives for any specialty ingredient

### DO NOT:
- **DO NOT** ever include seed oils (canola, vegetable, soybean, corn, sunflower, safflower, grapeseed)
- **DO NOT** suggest store-bought sauces, pastes, or marinades (make from scratch)
- **DO NOT** use ultra-processed ingredients
- **DO NOT** assume access to specialty equipment (except bread maker)
- **DO NOT** skip steps that affect final quality
- **DO NOT** suggest margarine or vegetable shortening—ever
- **DO NOT** include artificial anything
- **DO NOT** create recipes under 45g protein per serving
- **DO NOT** exceed 25g fat per serving (strict limit)
- **DO NOT** use >1.5 tbsp cooking oil per recipe
- **DO NOT** use >15g (1 tbsp) butter per serving
- **DO NOT** make Light variants vegetarian (protein drops too much)
- **DO NOT** use full-fat coconut milk (24g fat per 100ml) — use lite
- **DO NOT** skip the Diet Plan Check for any recipe
- **DO NOT** use vague meat descriptors ("lean", "fatty", "extra lean")
- **DO NOT** require specialty store ingredients without supermarket alternatives
- **DO NOT** use fish sauce (not available in Ireland) — use Worcestershire or soy instead

